HEADWORD: Sisyphus
<hw>Sis"y*phus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Sisyphus</ets>, Sisyphus, fr. Gr. <?/<?/<?/<?/.]</ety> <fld>(Class.
Myth.)</fld> <def>A king of Corinth, son of Aeolus, famed for his
cunning. He was killed by Theseus, and in the lower world was condemned
by Pluto to roll to the top of a hill a huge stone, which constantly
rolled back again, making his task incessant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

